    <custom_item>
      type        : CMD_EXEC
      description : "AOSX-14-004001 - The macOS system must be configured with system log files owned by root and group-owned by wheel or admin - Newsyslog"
      info        : "System logs should only be readable by root or admin users. System logs frequently contain sensitive information that could be used by an attacker. Setting the correct owner mitigates this risk."
      solution    : "For any log file that returns an incorrect owner or group value, run the following command:

/usr/bin/sudo chown root:wheel [log file]

